column16: Meterpreter, Zenmap, Armitage,Ettercap, Maltego, SQLi Helper, Socail Engineering toolkit. These are the tools which are used to scan and map networks and PCs based on their IP addreses and look for the vulnerabilities in them. Ettercap is also used to sniff networks and poison ARP caches and spoof DNS replies to computers in your network, providing us acces to all the data entered to a website by a user, without his knowledge. Meterpreter is used to get into the command shell of a victim and keep a complete track on its activities. You can also create phishing pages using SET. These softwares showed us how vulnerable the computer actually is and how we should take steps to secure our PCs.

column34: My favourite CSI event of last year, which was also my favourite tech event of !st year, is Hardwire. In the second round, we used a bread board to build a resistor circuit aand watched our LED glow without burning out. It was my first experience of building a circuit with a bread board, and it was super fun. The last round was my favourite, where each of us 3 team mates were given an individual problem statement, and each of our answer was a key to solving the final puzzle. My problem statement was related to number series, and I still remember communicating my answer to my team mate through Morse code. Overall it was a great event, and we were the runner ups. It was also really nice interacting with seniors like Yaamika and Mohak, who seemed to genuinely want us to learn something from the event. Also, among the many events I attended CSI was most prompt in giving us our certificates and prizes.

Frankly speaking the best part of the whole competition was Contraption (2nd Round) because it tested our skills under stress as we were supposed to do the whole thing in just 2 hours. We made through that too but yeah it was the best realisation of the importance of team work in my life. Now came the jackpot. We made through the second round too. The problem statement for final round was to build up a hydraulic crane using syringes and icecream sticks. Damn, the problem statement was challenging. It further ignited me from within to take up this challenge and finish it off in style. So we started building it up with great efforts. We sat with it till 5 a.m. in the morning to finish it. We got a lot of applaud from CSI members for our crane which was actually an amazing thing. I wasn't able to believe myself that we did it...Yes we did it..!!
